132 10. (1) Beginning July 1, 2010, any motor vehicle
133 dealer licensed under section 301.560 engaged in the
134 business of selling motor vehicles or trailers shall apply
135 to the director of revenue for authority to collect and
136 remit the sales tax required under this section on all motor
137 vehicles sold by the motor vehicle dealer. A motor vehicle
138 dealer receiving authority to collect and remit the tax is

SB 1632 6
139 subject to all provisions under sections 144.010 to
140 144.525. Any motor vehicle dealer authorized to collect and
141 remit sales taxes on motor vehicles under this subsection
142 shall be entitled to deduct and retain an amount equal to
143 two percent of the motor vehicle sales tax pursuant to
144 section 144.140. Any amount of the tax collected under this
145 subsection that is retained by a motor vehicle dealer
146 pursuant to section 144.140 shall not constitute state
147 revenue. In no event shall revenues from the general
148 revenue fund or any other state fund be utilized to
149 compensate motor vehicle dealers for their role in
150 collecting and remitting sales taxes on motor vehicles. In
151 the event this subsection or any portion thereof is held to
152 violate Article IV, Section 30(b) of the Missouri
153 Constitution, no motor vehicle dealer shall be authorized to
154 collect and remit sales taxes on motor vehicles under this
155 section. No motor vehicle dealer shall seek compensation
156 from the state of Missouri or its agencies if a court of
157 competent jurisdiction declares that the retention of two
158 percent of the motor vehicle sales tax is unconstitutional
159 and orders the return of such revenues.
160 (2) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the
161 contrary, when a motor vehicle, trailer, boat, or other
162 titled personal property is sold by a licensed Missouri
163 dealer to a purchaser who is not a resident of this state,
164 and the vehicle is delivered to or picked up at the dealer's
165 Missouri location, the dealer shall collect and remit
166 Missouri state and local sales tax according to law at the
167 rate applicable at the dealer's place of business. The
168 provisions of this subdivision shall apply regardless of
169 whether the purchaser intends to title or register the
170 vehicle in another state. The dealer shall not be required

SB 1632 7
171 to determine the tax rate of the purchaser's state of
172 residence.
173 11. (1) Every motor vehicle dealer licensed under
174 section 301.560, as soon as technologically possible
175 following the development and maintenance of a modernized,
176 integrated system for the titling of vehicles, issuance and
177 renewal of vehicle registrations, issuance and renewal of
178 driver's licenses and identification cards, and perfection
179 and release of liens and encumbrances on vehicles, to be
180 funded by the motor vehicle administration technology fund
181 as created in section 301.558, shall collect and remit the
182 sales tax required under this section on all motor vehicles,
183 boats, and outboard motors that such dealer sells as
184 directed by the director of revenue. In collecting and
185 remitting this sales tax, motor vehicle dealers shall be
186 subject to all applicable provisions under sections 144.010
187 to 144.527.
188 (2) The director of revenue may promulgate all
189 necessary rules and regulations for the administration of
190 this subsection. Any rule or portion of a rule, as that
191 term is defined in section 536.010, that is created under
192 the authority delegated in this subsection shall become
193 effective only if it complies with and is subject to all of
194 the provisions of chapter 536 and, if applicable, section
195 536.028. This subsection and chapter 536 are nonseverable
196 and if any of the powers vested with the general assembly
197 pursuant to chapter 536 to review, to delay the effective
198 date, or to disapprove and annul a rule are subsequently
199 held unconstitutional, then the grant of rulemaking
200 authority and any rule proposed or adopted after August 28,
201 2023, shall be invalid and void.

