307 (53) "Saddlemount combination", a combination of
308 vehicles in which a truck or truck tractor tows one or more
309 trucks or truck tractors, each connected by a saddle to the
310 frame or fifth wheel of the vehicle in front of it. The
311 "saddle" is a mechanism that connects the front axle of the
312 towed vehicle to the frame or fifth wheel of the vehicle in
313 front and functions like a fifth wheel kingpin connection.
314 When two vehicles are towed in this manner the combination
315 is called a "double saddlemount combination". When three

SB 1632 18
316 vehicles are towed in this manner, the combination is called
