1 301.030. 1. The director shall provide for the
2 retention of license plates by the owners of motor vehicles,
3 other than commercial motor vehicles, and shall establish a
4 system of registration on a monthly series basis to
5 distribute the work of registering motor vehicles as
6 uniformly as practicable throughout the twelve months of the
7 calendar year. For the purpose of assigning license plate
8 numbers, each type of motor vehicle shall be considered a
9 separate class. [Commencing July 1, 1949,] Motor vehicles,
10 other than commercial motor vehicles, shall be registered
11 for a period of twelve consecutive calendar months. [There
12 are established twelve registration periods, each of which
13 shall start on the first day of each calendar month of the
14 year and shall end on the last date of the twelfth month
15 from the date of beginning.] Fees for the renewal of
16 noncommercial motor vehicle registrations shall be payable
17 no later than the last day of the month [that follows the
18 twelfth month] of the expired registration period. No
19 [delinquent renewal penalty shall be assessed under section
20 301.050, and no] violation shall be issued under section
21 301.020 for an expired registration[, prior to the second
22 month that follows the twelfth month of the expired
23 registration period] before the last day of the month of
24 expiration.
25 2. Motor vehicles, other than commercial motor
26 vehicles, operated for the first time upon the public
27 highways of this state, to and including the fifteenth day
28 of any given month, shall be subject to registration and
29 payment of a fee for the twelve-month period commencing the
30 first day of the month of such operation; motor vehicles,

SB 1632 30
31 other than commercial motor vehicles, operated for the first
32 time on the public highways of this state after the
33 fifteenth day of any given month shall be subject to
34 registration and payment of a fee for the twelve-month
35 period commencing the first day of the next following
36 calendar month.
37 3. All commercial motor vehicles and trailers, except
38 those licensed under section 301.035 and those operated
39 under agreements as provided for in sections 301.271 to
40 301.279, shall be registered either on a calendar year basis
41 or on a prorated basis as provided in this section. The
42 fees for commercial motor vehicles, trailers, semitrailers,
43 and driveaway vehicles, other than those to be operated
44 under agreements as provided for in sections 301.271 to
45 301.279 shall be payable not later than the last day of
46 February of each year, except when such vehicle is licensed
47 between April first and July first the fee shall be three-
48 fourths the annual fee, when licensed between July first and
49 October first the fee shall be one-half the annual fee and
50 when licensed on or after October first the fee shall be one-
51 fourth the annual fee. Such license plates shall be made
52 with fully reflective material with a common color scheme
53 and design, shall be clearly visible at night, and shall be
54 aesthetically attractive, as prescribed by section 301.130.
55 Local commercial motor vehicle license plates may also be so
56 stamped, marked or designed as to indicate they are to be
57 used only on local commercial motor vehicles and, in
58 addition to such stamp, mark or design, the letter "F" shall
59 also be displayed on local commercial motor vehicle license
60 plates issued to motor vehicles used for farm or farming
61 transportation operations as defined in section 301.010 in
62 the manner prescribed by the advisory committee established

SB 1632 31
63 in section 301.129. In addition, all commercial motor
64 vehicle license plates may be so stamped or marked with a
65 letter, figure or other emblem as to indicate the gross
66 weight for which issued.
67 4. The director shall, upon application, issue
68 registration and license plates for nine thousand pounds
69 gross weight for property-carrying commercial motor vehicles
70 referred to herein, upon payment of the fees prescribed for
71 twelve thousand pounds gross weight as provided in section
72 301.057.
73 5. Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the
74 contrary, any motorcycle or motortricycle registration
75 issued by the Missouri department of revenue shall expire on
76 June thirtieth.
