123 5. The department of revenue shall not use, collect,
124 obtain, share, or retain biometric data nor shall the
125 department use biometric technology to produce a driver's
126 license or nondriver's license or to uniquely identify
127 licensees or license applicants. This subsection shall not
128 apply to digital images nor licensee signatures required for
129 the issuance of driver's licenses and nondriver's licenses
130 or for the use of software for purposes of combating fraud,
131 or to biometric data collected from employees of the
132 department of revenue, employees of the office of
133 administration who provide information technology support to
